According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Self-driving Cars Market was valued at USD 27.48 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 34.92 billion in 2026 to USD 312.45 billion by 2034, exhibiting an impressive CAGR of 31.4% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing remarkable momentum as advancements in artificial intelligence, sensor technologies, and connected mobility continue to redefine the future of transportation. Autonomous vehicles are rapidly transitioning from experimental pilot programs to commercial deployment, supported by increasing investments from automotive manufacturers, technology companies, and governments. Improvements in LiDAR, radar, high-resolution cameras, edge computing, and vehicle-to-everything (V2X) communication are making autonomous driving systems more reliable, scalable, and commercially viable across passenger transportation, logistics, and mobility services.
